I investigated the ticked created by Bruce regrading Group mgmt/Program mgm. 

I thought that might have to do with blocking call, but I confirmed that the calls themselves are non-blocking, 
so the slowness is not due to threading or I/O contention at the application layer.

So having ruled out application code is not blocking, the overall response time could be influenced by database query performance.

I recommend we revisit the queries and Use EXPLAIN (or EXPLAIN ANALYZE) on them to identify missing indexes, full table scans, 
or the quite too often culprit inefficient joins.

Review queries generated by Spring Data — since the application uses Spring Data and not all queries are native (other are JPQL)

